Nigeria Plans to Expand Port Facilities, BusinessDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-05-27T08:28:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/nigeria-plans-to-expand-port-facilities-businessday-says.html
Nigeria plans to expand and modernize
its port facilities to manage an anticipated jump in cargo,
 BusinessDay  reported, citing the managing director of the
Nigeria Ports Authority,  Omar Suleiman .  The West African country is the biggest market for goods on
the continent and its ports are also a transit for landlocked
neighbors like Niger and Chad Republics, the Lagos-based
newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 